ion in the commonwealth and a great opportunity to see some exciting work being done by many of our brightest high school students  Winners of the VSSEF will go on to represent Virginia at the Intel International Science and Engineering Fair  Projects will be grouped into 17 different categories  1  Animal Science 2  Behavioral and Social Science 3  Biochemistry 4  Cellular and Molecular Biology 5  Chemistry 6  Computer Science 7  Earth and Planetary Science 8  Energy and Transportation 9  Engineering  Electrical and Mechanical 10  Engineering  Material and Bioengineering 11  Environmental Management 12  Environmental Sciences 13  Mathematical Sciences 14  Medicine and Health Science 15  Microbiology 16  Physics and Astronomy 17  Plant Sciences If you have expertise in any of these areas  Ph D  research experience  etc  and would be willing to serve as a judge  please contact MAJ Geoff Cox    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 